Will you ever have children?
Do You Hear the Pipes, Cthulhu - Khaos   (Um?  Are you trying to tell me that it's pointless having kids because they'll just be eaten by something from outside sanity?  Is that it?)

The Loverboy
Random Gentle Love Master (RGLMm)

Well-liked. Well-established. You are The Loverboy. Loverboys thrive in committed, steady relationships--as opposed to, say, Playboys, who want sex without too much attachment.

You've had many relationships and nearly all of them have been successful. You're a nice guy, you know the ropes, and even if you can be a little hasty with decisions, most girls think of you as a total catch. Your hastiness comes off as spontaneity most of the time anyhow, making you especially popular in your circle of friends, too.

Your exact opposite:
The Billy Goat

Deliberate Brutal Sex Dreamer
You know not to make the typical Loverboy mistake of choosing someone who appreciates your good humor and popularity, but who offers nothing in return. You belong with someone outgoing, independent, and creative. Otherwise, you'll get bored. And then instead of surprising him with flowers or a practical joke, you'll surprise him by leaving.


ALWAYS AVOID: The Billy Goat

CONSIDER: The Boy Next Door, The Loverboy

Business was terrible on Friday.  Which is to say that I didn't sell a bloody thing.  I did go and spread cash lovin's around the other dealers though.  Saturday and Sunday picked up though, and I ended up about doubling my investment for this year, so no complaints overall.  I think I may have to revise prices for next year.  The location was pretty nice, even if it was in the corner... had the Rage person's bookstore on one side, and Teaselbone and Dalia on the other, who're both pretty cool people when they're not ninjing over my chair (ninjing: to ninj like a ninja).
The rest of the con, when I could get away from my table, was highly entertaining.  I got a nice bag of swag, went to a few panels done by Winged Siamese (and fanboyed out some gift art for her inspired by the remark about 'having a skeleton mack on someone' that was said during her Horror Drawing panel).  Draw or Die was a blast- some of the most incoherent stuff I've ever seen, and I helped.
And now, Halloween- all the freaks in costumes shall pale in comparison.  C'est la vie.  The horror movie marathon for this year is the Amityville Horror (1, 2 and 3-D).  Amityviiille!

They Live.

Your Birthdate: September 21
Being born on the 21st day of the month (3 energy) is likely to add a good bit of vitality to your life. The energy of 3 allows you bounce back rapidly from setbacks, physical or mental. There is a restlessness in your nature, but you seem to be able to portray an easygoing, "couldn't care less" attitude. You have a natural ability to express yourself in public, and you always make a very good impression. Good with words, you excel in writing, speaking, and possibly singing. You are energetic and always a good conversationalist. You have a keen imagination, but you tend to scatter your energies and become involved with too may superficial matters. Your mind is practical and rational despite this tendency to jump about. You are affectionate and loving, but very sensitive. You are subject to rapid ups and downs.

________8P____________-KP

-QP_____-5W____-6S____-IX

_______|3C|___________-9S

________QW____________-III

1. Atmosphere: 5 of Wands (reversed): The five of wands represents competition and violence; reversed indicates victory or an end to such things.  Breaking through a logjam.
2. Opposition: 3 of Cups (crosses): Overindulgence; empty pleasures; success spoiled.
3. Foundation: Queen of Wands: Uses and inspires creativity; growth and love; spontaneous action
4. Recent past: Queen of Pentacles (reversed): Neglected duties; helplessness and dependence
5. Possible future: 8 of Pentacles: Preparation; self-discipline; learning; employment
6. Near future: 6 of Swords (reversed): Stuck.  No way out (at least at present)
7. Internal: III Empress (reversed): Poor health; frustration in creativity or creation; maternal problems
8. External: 9 of Swords (reversed): Healing with time; patience; end of nightmare or depression
9. Hopes/Fears: IX Hermit (reversed): Immaturity; refusal to listen to elders; desire to be with others
10. Outcome: King of Pentacles (reversed): Misuse of talents or resources; financial problems; stupidly stubborn

Interpretation: The whole spread focuses on the fine line between success and overindulgence.  The cross section shows a cycle of creativity and work followed by an empty period.  The staff area suggests that those around can help through the slumps, if they're listened to.  The outcome in 10 and the future in 5 conflict with each other, suggesting that either might be arrived at.

For various reasons- practice, mostly, and so I'd have something to show here other than an unending string of quizzes- I'm posting a tarot spread.  Perhaps this'll become a weekly thing, I don't know.  A standard celtic cross spread.  The deck is Robin Wood, because it's always been a favorite.  Question is open, pertaining to the world at large.

_______-IV____________9P

-AC_____2W_____QW____-VIII

_______|QS|___________8P

_______-8C___________-QC

1. Atmosphere: 2 of Wands: Independence; control of the situation; creative potential
2. Opposition: Queen of Swords (crosses): Sharp observation and critique; self-reliance
3. Foundation: 8 of Cups (reversed): End of searching; material focus; finding joy in success
4. Recent past: Ace of Cups (reversed): A dry spell; feeling drained; emotional emptiness
5. Possible future: IV Emperor (reversed): Loss of control; injury; over reliance on cold reason
     Perhaps worth noting that my personality card (determined by adding birth month, day and year together and then adding the digits of the result) comes out to 4, for the Emperor, and that I've never been particularly happy about it.
6. Near future: Queen of Wands: Personal power; spontaneous action; creativity, inspiration, growth
7. Internal: Queen of Cups (reversed): Perverse; fickle; relies on fantasies
8. External: 8 of Pentacles: Self-discipline; practice; preparation
9. Hopes/Fears: VIII Strength (reversed): Discord between instinct and intellect; weakness; abuse of power
10. Outcome: 9 of Pentacles: Solitary leisure; simple pleasures; hobbies

Interesting that the positive or negative orientation follows suits; all the wands and pentacles are upright, all the cups and major arcana are reversed.  The one sword in the spread is in a neutral position.

Interpretation: Seeks independence but must avoid relying solely on self.  Success in the past but currently in a slump; future may hold a similar cycle of energy followed by apathy, perhaps stronger than the current one.  Strong conflict between internal desires and the external need for discipline.  If lack of strength can be overcome, may be able to find a middle ground between work and play.

If anyone else reading this knows tarot and has anything to add to the interpretation, please feel free to comment.

I Am A: True Neutral Elf Mage

Alignment:
True Neutral characters are very rare. They believe that balance is the most important thing, and will not side with any other force. They will do whatever is necessary to preserve that balance, even if it means switching allegiances suddenly.

Race:
Elves are the eldest of all races, although they are generally a bit smaller than humans. They are generally well-cultured, artistic, easy-going, and because of their long lives, unconcerned with day-to-day activities that other races frequently concern themselves with. Elves are, effectively, immortal, although they can be killed. After a thousand years or so, they simply pass on to the next plane of existance.

Primary Class:
Mages harness the magical energies for their own use. Spells, spell books, and long hours in the library are their loves. While often not physically strong, their mental talents can make up for this.

Secondary Class:
Monks are strange and generally not understood by the world at large. They live apart from people, and follow strict codes that restrain their behavior and lifestyle. They have an exceptionally calm outlook on life, and generally do not resort to violence unless absolutely necessary. Even when they do, their code of conduct forbids the use of all weapons - except their hands. As such, monks are extremely skilled at hand-to-hand combat, and no other style.
